BEHAVIUOR OF THE SALES
1. What is selling the most?
We sell three main types of products, and they are all doing well:

Technology (Gadgets): This is our biggest winner, bringing in over ₹7.86 Crores.

Furniture & Office Supplies: These two are almost equal, bringing in ₹6.98 Crores and ₹6.76 Crores. It is a very balanced mix.

2. Which areas are buying?
The West & East: These are our strongest markets, bringing in ₹6.82 Crores and ₹6.38 Crores.

The South: This is our smallest area right now at ₹3.68 Crores. We have a good chance to grow more there.

3. Who are our customers?
Regular People (Consumers): They are the backbone of our business. They spent over ₹10.92 Crores.

Offices (Corporate): Big companies and home offices make up the rest of our sales.

4. Understanding the "Big Orders" (Outliers)
When we look at the numbers, there is an interesting gap:

The Usual Sale: Most of our customers spend around ₹5,125.

The "Giant" Order: We had one single customer spend ₹21.29 Lakhs!

The Gap: Because of this one massive order, our "average" looks like it is ₹21,620.

In simple words: Our business runs on many small daily orders, but every now and then, a "Big Fish" (Outlier) comes in and pushes our total sales very high.

BEHAVIOUR OF THE PROFIT

1. Which Products are Making Money?
We have three main categories, and there is a big difference in how much profit they bring home:

Technology: This is our gold mine. It earned a huge profit of ₹1.36 Crores.

Office Supplies: This is also very strong, bringing in ₹1.15 Crores.

Furniture: This is the weakest area. Even though we sell a lot of furniture, the actual profit is very low—only ₹17.35 Lakhs.

2. Which Areas are Most Profitable?
The West & East: These two are doing amazing. The West earned ₹1.02 Crores and the East earned ₹86 Lakhs in profit.

Central & South: These areas are okay, but they make much less profit (around ₹37 Lakhs to ₹44 Lakhs) compared to the others.

3. Who is Giving Us the Most Profit?
Regular People (Consumers): They provide the most profit, over ₹1.26 Crores.

Offices (Corporate): They bring in about ₹86.5 Lakhs.

Home Offices: They are the smallest group but still profitable at ₹56.7 Lakhs.

